layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Tax-Efficient Retirement Strategies | Capital Wealth Lehi, UT"
description: "Minimize taxes in retirement with strategic planning. Roth conversions, withdrawal strategies, tax-loss harvesting, and IRMAA avoidance. Expert tax planning in Utah."
breadcrumbs:
  - { name: "Home", url: "/" }
  - { name: "Services", url: "/services/" }
  - { name: "Tax-Efficient Retirement Strategies", url: "/services/tax-planning/" }
faqSchema:
  - question: "Do you prepare tax returns?"
    answer: "We focus on tax strategy and planning, not tax preparation. We work closely with your CPA to develop and implement strategies, then they handle the actual return filing. Think of it as: we build the plan, they execute the paperwork."
  - question: "When should I do a Roth conversion?"
    answer: "The best time is typically during low-income years before RMDs start (ages 60-72), or after retirement but before Social Security begins. We model your specific situation to identify the optimal years and amounts to convert."
  - question: "What is IRMAA and how do I avoid it?"
    answer: "IRMAA (Income-Related Monthly Adjustment Amount) is a Medicare surcharge for higher earners. We help you manage your income to stay below the thresholds through strategic withdrawal timing, Roth conversions in low-income years, and charitable giving strategies."
  - question: "How much can I save with tax planning?"
    answer: "The average client with proper multi-year tax planning saves $200,000+ over their lifetime compared to reactive, year-by-year tax preparation. The exact amount depends on your income sources, account types, and time horizon."
  - question: "What's the difference between tax planning and tax preparation?"
    answer: "Tax preparation looks backward and files last year's return. Tax planning looks forward and builds multi-year strategies to minimize your lifetime tax liability. We do planning; your CPA does preparation."
---

